<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-147-117 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 876 346</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 27 1991 n422 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Campaign to boost channel image gets underway. (ABCD: TheMicrocomputer Industry Association leads public relations effort)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sweeney, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ABCD: The Microcomputer Industry Association leads an effort toimprove vendor relations within the computer industry.andP;  It alsoleads a public relations campaign designed to improve the image ofthe value-added resellers and dealer channel.andP;  Specifics include a$1 million budget to be used to increase awareness in the industryof dealer effectiveness, reverse negative images of resellers andfoster cooperative agreements among computer makers, consumers anddealers.andP;  Other goals are to counter enormous advertisingresources of the mail-order channel, a relatively small part ofthe industry and correct any false impressions created by the fewcomputer retailing superstores.andP;  Quantitative research involvingsurveys of users conducted by The Gallup Organization Inc,qualitative research and information from focus groups andindustry consultants.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Value-added resellersPublic RelationsABCD: The Microcomputer Industry AssociationComputer industryDealers and AgentsVendor Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>